{"TopicId":161878,"ForumId":29,"TopicTitle":"Killing kerbals softly","CreatedByName":"garwel","CreatedById":141813,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-10T10:08:02Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"garwel","CreatedById":141813,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-10T10:08:02Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI asked this question in the other thread, but got no answer, so asking here.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI need to be able to kill a kerbal (I have an instance of\u00A0ProtoCrewMember), which can be loaded or unloaded.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nUsing ProtoCrewMember.Die()\u00A0causes an NRE in flight scene and doesn\u0027t remove the portrait.\u00A0For now,\u00A0I\u0027ve been using this code (PCM is an instance of ProtoCrewMember):\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cpre class=\u0022ipsCode prettyprint lang-c prettyprinted\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022kwd\u0022\u003Eif\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pln\u0022\u003E \u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pun\u0022\u003E(\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pln\u0022\u003EPCM\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pun\u0022\u003E.\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pln\u0022\u003Eseat \u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pun\u0022\u003E!=\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pln\u0022\u003E null\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pun\u0022\u003E)\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pln\u0022\u003E PCM\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pun\u0022\u003E.\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pln\u0022\u003Eseat\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pun\u0022\u003E.\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pln\u0022\u003Epart\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pun\u0022\u003E.\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan\u003ERemoveCrewmember\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pun\u0022\u003E(\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pln\u0022\u003EPCM\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pun\u0022\u003E);\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pln\u0022\u003E\nPCM\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pun\u0022\u003E.\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pln\u0022\u003ErosterStatus \u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pun\u0022\u003E=\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pln\u0022\u003E \u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan\u003EProtoCrewMember\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pun\u0022\u003E.\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan\u003ERosterStatus\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pun\u0022\u003E.\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan\u003EDead\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pun\u0022\u003E;\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/pre\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHowever, this doesn\u0027t always work well. Sometimes, I have a portrait replaced with white noise but the box still displayed and the kerbal visible in IVA. What\u0027s worse, this code\u00A0doesn\u0027t seem to work from \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Space Center\u0022\u003EKSC\u003C/abbr\u003E at all. In any case, even if it kinda works, the deceased kerbals simply disappear from the roster and are not seen in the Lost tab.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo, what is the best way to kill a kerbal?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-06-10T13:01:33Z\u0022 title=\u002206/10/2017 01:01  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EJune 10, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by garwel\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"ARS","CreatedById":168061,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-10T12:24:47Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSummon a kraken. The kerbal will transcend their corporeal form\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"wasml","CreatedById":120438,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-11T00:41:02Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI can only suggest you look at the code for some mod that does this - I think a few of the life support mods can kill a Kerbal - like \u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/137227-122-kerbalism-v128/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003EKerbalism\u003C/a\u003E, \u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/146465-13-tac-life-support-v0132-release-29th-may-2017/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003ETAC-Life Support\u003C/a\u003E, and possibly \u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/105202-13-usi-life-support-050/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Umbra Space Industries (a collection of mods)\u0022\u003EUSI\u003C/abbr\u003E-Life Support\u003C/a\u003E(configurable?).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"JPLRepo","CreatedById":114736,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-11T07:13:23Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI already answered this where the same question was posted in this thread.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/7542-the-official-unoffical-quothelp-a-fellow-plugin-developerquot-thread/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0026amp;comment=3087228\u0026amp;embedComment=3087228\u0026amp;embedDo=findComment\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"garwel","CreatedById":141813,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-11T13:54:25Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223087461\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022161878\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221497141662\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022120438\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022wasml\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n13 hours ago, wasml said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI can only suggest you look at the code for some mod that does this - I think a few of the life support mods can kill a Kerbal - like \u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/137227-122-kerbalism-v128/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003EKerbalism\u003C/a\u003E, \u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/146465-13-tac-life-support-v0132-release-29th-may-2017/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003ETAC-Life Support\u003C/a\u003E, and possibly \u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/105202-13-usi-life-support-050/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Umbra Space Industries (a collection of mods)\u0022\u003EUSI\u003C/abbr\u003E-Life Support\u003C/a\u003E(configurable?).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027ve looked at \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Umbra Space Industries (a collection of mods)\u0022\u003EUSI\u003C/abbr\u003E-LS and they basically do the same thing (plus mark vessel crew as dirty). Tried to emulate that, but it didn\u0027t help. Will try what JPLRepo has suggested and see. But the problem is usually with non-loaded vessels.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"TheRagingIrishman","CreatedById":165004,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-11T16:15:46Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223087884\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022161878\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221497189265\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022141813\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022garwel\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, garwel said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027ve looked at \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Umbra Space Industries (a collection of mods)\u0022\u003EUSI\u003C/abbr\u003E-LS and they basically do the same thing (plus mark vessel crew as dirty). Tried to emulate that, but it didn\u0027t help. Will try what JPLRepo has suggested and see. But the problem is usually with non-loaded vessels.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou could just wait until you visit the ship and then kill them\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"artwhaley","CreatedById":118388,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-13T21:48:38Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223087672\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022161878\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221497165203\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022114736\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022JPLRepo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 6/11/2017 at 2:13 AM, JPLRepo said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI already answered this where the same question was posted in this thread.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/7542-the-official-unoffical-quothelp-a-fellow-plugin-developerquot-thread/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0026amp;comment=3087228\u0026amp;embedComment=3087228\u0026amp;embedDo=findComment\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI hate that thread! \u00A0lol. \u00A0 There\u0027s so much great stuff buried so deep in it! \u00A0I wish all those issues were in their own threads so they were easier to find!\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"theJesuit","CreatedById":122369,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-13T22:07:01Z","Content":"\n\u003Cdiv style=\u0022color:#222222;\u0022\u003E\nApologies to the Fugees \u00A0\u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=oKOtzIo-uYw\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://www.youtube.com/watch?v=oKOtzIo-uYw\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv style=\u0022color:#222222;\u0022\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv style=\u0022color:#222222;\u0022\u003E\nTapping the board with your fingers.\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv style=\u0022color:#222222;\u0022\u003E\nPlaying with life by key\u00A0strokes.\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv style=\u0022color:#222222;\u0022\u003E\nKilling them softly with your code;\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv style=\u0022color:#222222;\u0022\u003E\nKilling them softly, with your code;\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv style=\u0022color:#222222;\u0022\u003E\nPlaying their whole life by key strokes\u003Cbr\u003E\nKilling them softly with your code.\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv style=\u0022color:#222222;\u0022\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv style=\u0022color:#222222;\u0022\u003E\nI saw them only proto, I saw them in C sharp,\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv style=\u0022color:#222222;\u0022\u003E\nAnd sent them up in rockets, keys were played\u00A0like a harp,\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv style=\u0022color:#222222;\u0022\u003E\nAnd there they were, these kerbals, light beams sent to my eyes...\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027ll see myself out then.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"garwel","CreatedById":141813,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-14T05:16:33Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223088009\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022161878\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221497197746\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022165004\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022TheRagingIrishman\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 6/11/2017 at 7:15 PM, TheRagingIrishman said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou could just wait until you visit the ship and then kill them\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIn some edge cases (the kerbal is in a vessel landed on Kerbin) it can make \u0022dead\u0022 kerbals recoverable, with unpredictable consequences. Plus, having an apparently dead kerbal marked as alive and assigned in the roster can affect other mods, e.g. life support. I\u0027ll see if I can find a way around it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}